dcterms:description: The Genomics of Drug Sensitivity in Cancer (GDSC) database provides open data for researchers in phenotypic screening to test their models and methods. It includes information on the relationship among many types of cancer and various anti-cancer drugs, with cancer cell lines described by their genetic features and drugs identified by their compound IDs.
dcterms:title: Genomics of Drug Sensitivity in Cancer (GDSC)

dcterms:description: The Cancer Cell Line Encyclopedia (CCLE) is a resource that provides genomic data and drug sensitivity information for a large number of cancer cell lines, facilitating research in cancer biology and drug discovery.
dcterms:title: Cancer Cell Line Encyclopedia (CCLE)

dcterms:description: The Library of Integrated Network-based Cellular Signatures (LINCS) is a program that catalogs human cellular responses to various perturbations, providing a resource for understanding cellular behavior and drug responses.
dcterms:title: LINCS (Library of Integrated Network-based Cellular Signatures)
